org.gradoop.temporal.model.impl.operators.keyedgrouping.keys

Class TimeStampKeyFunction<T extends TemporalElement>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gradoop.temporal.model.impl.operators.keyedgrouping.keys.TimeStampKeyFunction<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the elements to group.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, KeyFunction<T,Long>

    public class TimeStampKeyFunction<T extends TemporalElement>
extends Object
implements KeyFunction<T,Long>
    A key function extracting a time stamp of a TemporalElement.

    An optional TemporalField parameter can be given to this key function. In this case the time stamp will be converted to a date (with a time zone set to UTC) and the field (e. g. month) will be extracted from that date.

    When no TemporalField is given, the time stamp will be used as is, in milliseconds since unix epoch.

    The final grouping key will be stored on the super element as a property with key time_INTERVAL_FIELD_CALCULATEDFIELD where INTERVAL is the TimeDimension, FIELD the TimeDimension.Field and CALCULATEDFIELD the TemporalField extracted from the element. When no TemporalField is given, the property will just be called time_INTERVAL_FIELD.
